r than} 28. Qe3 Ba6 $11 {, is going to be revealed already on the next move.}) 28... Kh7 29. Qe3 Bf5 ({In the new situation 29... Ba6 will eventually lose the b-pawn after 30.Ne4, while} 29... a5 $4 {is just disastrous because of} 30. Nb3 $1 $18) 30. Nc4 {It is preferable to preserve the rooks on the board, as shown by} (30. a5 Ne6 31. Rxc7 Qxc7 $11 {Firouzja - Nihal, Warsaw, 2021}) ({or} 30. g4 Be6 31. Ne4 Nxe4 32. Rxc7 Qxc7 33. Qxe4+ g6 34. Qxb4 Qd8 35. h5 gxh5 36. gxh5 Qg5+ $11) 30... Qd3 31. Be2 (31. Ne5 $143 Qxe3 32. fxe3 f6) 31... Qxe3 32. Nxe3 Be6 33. a5 $14 *

