...Nd5}) 15. a5 Nd7 16. e4 Bc6 17. Rfd1 Rfd8 18. Qc2 Nf6 19. Ne5 Bb5 20. Rac1 Rac8 21. Qc3 $14 {with stable central preponderance.}) (11... a5 $5 {is probably the most critical continuation.} 12. Rfd1 (12. Rfe1 Bb4) 12... h6 {is the natural follow-up of move 10 -} (12... Bb4 13. Ne5 $1 Bxg2 14. Kxg2 Nb6 15. Qb3 h6 16. Bxf6 (16. Be3 $5 Nbd5 17. Bd2) 16... Qxf6 17. Rac1 Qd8 18. e3 c6 19. h4 $14) (12... Bxf3 $2 {cannot be approved here -} 13. Bxf3 c6 14. e4 h6 15. Be3 $16 {Mareco - Vachier Lagrave, Chess.com INT, 2023}) 13. Bxf6 Nxf6 {and now:} 14. Qb3 $5 {is a crafty attempt to confuse the opponent:} (14. Ne5 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 c6 {looks rock-solid, for example} 16. e4 (16. e3 Bb4 17. Qe2 Qe7 18. Qf3 Rfd8 19. h4 Rac8 20. Ne4 Nxe4 21. Qxe4 Bd6 22. Nf3 Bb4 $11 {Dubov - Yu Yangyi, Chess.com INT, 2022}) 16... Bb4 (16... Qb6 $5) 17. Qe2 Qb6 18. Rac1 Rad8 19. Nf3 Rd7 $11 {Carlsen - Nakamura, Chess.com INT, 2022}) 14... Qb8 $1 {is Black's safest reply -} (14... Ra6 15. e3 Rb6 16. Qc2 $14 {[%csl Rb6]}) (14... Bb4 15. Ne5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 {is venomous either:} c6 {appeared in an earlier game, in which} (16... Qe7 {and in Vitiugov - Wei Yi, Lichess.org INT, 2021, White had the strong} 17. Na2 $1 c5 (17... Bd6 18. Qxb7 Rab8 19. Qf3 Bxe5 20. dxe5 Nd5 21. Nc3 $14) 18. Rac1 $14) 17. Na2 $1 {has not been missed.} Qd5+ $6 (17... c5 18. Rac1 $14) 18. Qxd5 Nxd5 19. e4 Nc7 20. Nxb4 axb4 21. Nd3 Na6 22. Kf3 Rfd8 23. Ke3 $16 {Grischuk - Adly, Chess.com INT, 2020}) 15. Rac1 (15. Ne5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 c6 {may just transpose}) 15... Rd8 16. Ne5 (16. e3 Be8 {[%cal Gc7c6]}) 16... Bxg2 17. Kxg2 c6 18. h4 Nd7 (18... Bb4 19. e3) 19. Nf3 Qc7 20. Qc2 Rac8 21. e3 $14 {/=/}) ({the insertion of} 11... Rc8 12. Rfe1 {[%cal Ge2e4] seems to favor White -} Ne4 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Qd3 $1 f5 ({or} 14... Nxc3 15. bxc3 f5 16. Qe3 Nb6 17. Ne5 {with firm grip on the center -} Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Nd5 19. Qd2 c5 20. a5 cxd4 21. cxd4 $14 {[%csl Ge5]}) 15. Nd2 $5 Nxd2 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Qxd2 c5 {has happened in Yezhel - Dziewonski, Krakow, 2023, now} 18. dxc5 Nxc5 19. Qe3 $14 {is keeping an eye on all Black's weaknesses.}) 12. Bxf6 (12. Bd2 a5 {is pretty safe for Black -} 13. Rfd1 (13. Qd3 Bb4) 13... Bb4 14. Qd3 Qe7 15. Be1 Rfd8 16. Qc2 Nb6 17. b3 Rac8 18. Rac1 Ba3 19. Ra1 Bb4 $11 {Aronian- Kramnik, Paris, 2016}) (12. Bf4 Bd6 $11) 12... Nxf6 13. a5 $5 {As we have seen in Chapter 21, this advance should suit the first player.} ({Another version of the plan for queenside expansion is} 13. b4 Bd5 $1 ({Black has reached the Carlsbad structure under worse conditions after} 13... Qd6 14. b5 axb5 15. axb5 Bd5 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Qb3 c6 18. e3 Nd7 19. bxc6 bxc6 20. Rfd1 Rfb8 21. Qc2 Bf6 22. Rxa8 Rxa8 23. Rc1 Ra6 24. Bf1 Rb6 {Giri - Sarana, Moscow, 2019} 25. h4 $14) 14. Nxd5 exd5 15. Qb3 c6 ({or} 15... Bd6 {[%cal Gd8e7] at once}) 16. e3 Bd6 (16... Ne4 17. Rfc1 Qd6 18. Rab1) 17. Rfc1 (17. Rfd1 Re8 18. b5 axb5 19. axb5 Rxa1 20. Rxa1 Qb6 $11 {Giri - Nepomniachtchi, chess24.com INT, 2020}) 17... Qe7 18. Rab1 Rfd8 19. Rc2 h5 20. h4 Ne4 $11 {Keymer - Esipenko, Biel, 2022.}) (13. Rfd1 a5 {- 11...a5.}) 13... Qd6 ({Now and then} 13... Bxf3 $6 {is of doubtful strategical value, which is confirmed by nearly every known practical example, e.g.} 14. Bxf3 c6 15. h4 ({for} 15. Rfd1 $14 {see Deac - Navara below}) 15... h5 16. e4 g6 17. Rfd1 Rc8 18. b4 $5 (18. Qb3 Qc7 {Wang Yue - Kryvoruchko, Antalya, 2013} 19. Ne2 Rfd8 20. Nf4 $14) 18... Qc7 19. Rac1 Rfd8 20. Qb3 $14) (13... Bd5 14. Qd3 {is hardly improving Black's position:} c5 (14... Bxf3 $6 15. Bxf3 c6 16. Qc4 Qc7 17. Rfd1 Rfd8 18. b4 Rac8 $6 (18... Rab8 $142) 19. Na4 e5 $2 20. Nb6 Rb8 21. d5 Qd6 22. dxc6 Qxd1+ 23. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 24. Kg2 bxc6 25. Bxc6 Rd4 26. Qxa6 Bxb4 27. Qa7 Rbd8 28. a6 $18 {Deac - Navara, Chess.com INT, 2020}) 15. dxc5 (15. e4 $6 Bc6) 15... Bxc5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Qb3 Qe7 18. Ne5 $14 {[%cal Ge5d3]}) 14. Rfd1 (14. Rfc1 Rac8 15. e3 Rfd8 16. Qe2 Bxf3 $6 ({the patient} 16... Bf8 {should have been preferred}) 17. Bxf3 c6 18. Na4 Nd7 19. Rc4 $14 {Inarkiev - Cheparinov, Monzon, 2016}) 14... Rfd8 (14... b5 {contains certain risk, after} 15. axb6 cxb6 {and the retreat} 16. Qd3 {the a6-pawn is really hanging.} Bb7 (16... Nd5 $6 17. Nxd5 Bxd5 18. Rxa6 Be4 19. Qb5 Rxa6 20. Qxa6 Qb4 21. Ne5 Bxg2 22. Kxg2 Qxb2 23. Nc6 Bg5 24. Qd3 Qa2 25. Rb1 Qd5+ 26. Qf3 $16 {Dubov - Gukesh, Krasnaya Polyana, 2021}) 17. Ne5 $1 (17. e4 Qb8 18. e5 Nd5 19. Nxd5 Bxd5 20. Rxa6 {took place in S. Ganguly - A. Onischuk, Astana, 2019, when Black could rely on compensation after} Rd8 $1 21. Rxa8 $140 Qxa8 $44) 17... Bxg2 (17... Qb8 18. Nc6 Qc7 19. Nxe7+ Qxe7 20. e4 $14 {[%cal Gd4d5,Gh2h4,Gd1d2]}) (17... Qc7 18. Rac1 $36) 18. Kxg2 b5 (18... Nd7 19. Nxd7 Qxd7 20. d5 $14) 19. Qf3 $14) 15. e3 Rab8 16. Qe2 Bf8 17. h4 $14 {/=/} *

